#: ../transitions.rst:121
msgid "The :guilabel:`Duration` property is a float value indicating the length of the transition in seconds. This is a Read-only property. This is calculated by: End - Start. To modify duration, you must edit the :guilabel:`Start` and/or :guilabel:`End` transition properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:124
msgid "**Usage Example:** Inspect the duration of a transition to ensure it fits a specific time slot in the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:125
msgid "**Tip:** Consider using the \"Duration\" property for transitions that need to match specific time intervals, such as dialogue or scenes."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:129
msgid "The :guilabel:`End` property defines the trimming point at the end of the transition in seconds, allowing you to control how much of the transition is visible in the timeline. Changing this property will impact the :guilabel:`Duration` transition property."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:132
msgid "**Usage Example:** Trimming the end of a transition to align with another clip or trimming off unwanted sections of the transition."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:133
msgid "**Tip:** Combine the \"Start\" and \"End\" properties to precisely control the visible portion of the transition."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:137
msgid "The :guilabel:`ID` property holds a randomly generated GUID (Globally Unique Identifier) assigned to each transition, ensuring its uniqueness. This is a Read-only property, and assigned by OpenShot when a transition is created."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:140
msgid "**Usage Example:** Referencing specific transitions within custom scripts or automation tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:141
msgid "**Tip:** While typically managed behind the scenes, understanding transition IDs can aid in advanced project customization."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:145
msgid "The :guilabel:`Track` property is an integer indicating the layer on which the transition is placed. Transitions on higher tracks are rendered above those on lower tracks."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:148
msgid "**Usage Example:** Arranging transitions in different layers for creating visual depth and complexity."
msgstr ""

#: ../transitions.rst:149
msgid "**Tip:** Use higher tracks for elements that need to appear above others, like text overlays or graphics."
msgstr ""
